        <a href="https://www.railstutorial.org/book"><em>Ruby on Rails Tutorial</em> book</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-section">
      <h3>ðŸ”§ Common Issues</h3>
      <p><strong>Database Connection Issues:</strong> Make sure your MySQL server is running and the database credentials are correct.</p>
      <p><strong>Migration Errors:</strong> Run <code>rake db:migrate</code> to apply pending migrations.</p>
      <p><strong>Asset Pipeline Issues:</strong> Try running <code>rake assets:precompile</code> in production.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-section">
      <h3>ðŸ“– Documentation</h3>
      <p>For comprehensive documentation and tutorials, visit the official Rails guides and the Rails Tutorial website.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="quick-links">
      <a href="https://www.railstutorial.org/help" class="quick-link">
        <h4>ðŸ“– Tutorial Help</h4>
        <p>Get help with the Rails Tutorial</p>
      </a>
      <a href="https://www.railstutorial.org/book" class="quick-link">
        <h4>ðŸ“š Rails Book</h4>
        <p>Complete Rails Tutorial book</p>
      </a>
      <a href="https://guides.rubyonrails.org/" class="quick-link">
        <h4>ðŸ“‹ Rails Guides</h4>
        <p>Official Rails documentation</p>
      </a>
    </div>
    
    <div class="nav-links">
      <a href="/static_pages/home">Home</a>
      <a href="/static_pages/about">About</a>
      <a href="/users">Users</a>
      <a href="/microposts">Microposts</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>